## Academic Template Features

This template includes specialized components and integrations for academic websites.

### @uniweb/scholar Integration

The foundation includes `@uniweb/scholar` for professional academic content:

```javascript
// Available imports in components
import { formatReference, CiteButton, DoiLink, AuthorList } from '@uniweb/scholar'
import { Math, Equation, EquationProvider } from '@uniweb/scholar/math'
import { CitationProvider, Citation, Bibliography } from '@uniweb/scholar/citations'
```

### Academic Components

#### PublicationList

Display publications with professional citation formatting.

```markdown
---
type: PublicationList
citationStyle: detailed    # detailed | apa | mla | chicago | ieee
groupBy: year              # none | year
showType: true             # Color-coded publication types
showCiteButton: true       # Copy citation button
showSearch: false
---

## Publications

#### journal

### Paper Title

Author One, Author Two, Author Three

Journal Name, Volume(Issue), Pages

2024

10.1234/doi.here

[PDF](#)
[Code](https://github.com)
```

**Content structure per publication:**
- H4 (####) before H3: Publication type (journal, conference, book, preprint)
- H3 (###): Paper title
- Paragraph 1: Authors
- Paragraph 2: Venue/Journal
- Paragraph 3: Year
- Paragraph 4: DOI (optional, just the identifier like `10.1234/example`)
- Links: PDF, code, slides, etc.

**Citation styles:**
| Style | Format |
|-------|--------|
| `detailed` | Title prominent, structured display |
| `apa` | APA 7th Edition |
| `mla` | MLA 9th Edition |
| `chicago` | Chicago Author-Date |
| `ieee` | IEEE numeric |

#### MathBlock

Display LaTeX equations with KaTeX rendering.

```markdown
---
type: MathBlock
showNumbers: true
background: white    # white | gray | dark
---

### Mathematical Foundations

# Section Title

Text with inline math like $E = mc^2$ and display math:

$$\int_0^\infty e^{-x^2} dx = \frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{2}$$

### Equation Name

\mathcal{L} = -\sum_{c=1}^{C} y_c \log(\hat{y}_c)

Description of the equation.
```

**Math syntax:**
- Inline: `$...$` within paragraphs
- Display: `$$...$$` for block equations
- Named equations: H3 heading + LaTeX in first paragraph

