### Publication Type Colors

The template defines semantic colors for publication types in `foundation/src/styles.css`:

```css
@theme {
  --color-journal: #3b82f6;     /* Blue */
  --color-conference: #8b5cf6;  /* Purple */
  --color-book: #22c55e;        /* Green */
  --color-preprint: #f59e0b;    /* Amber */
}
```

Use in components: `bg-journal`, `bg-conference`, `bg-book`, `bg-preprint`

### Adding Publications

1. Publications live in `site/pages/publications/` or inline on other pages
2. Each H3 section is one publication
3. Use H4 before H3 to set publication type
4. DOI is the 4th paragraph (just the identifier, not full URL)
5. The CiteButton lets visitors copy citations in any format

### Adding Math Content

1. Use the `MathBlock` component for equation-heavy sections
2. Inline math works in any paragraph with `$...$`
3. Named equations use H3 headings followed by LaTeX
4. Equations are numbered automatically within an `EquationProvider`

### Search

Search is enabled by default and indexes all content including:
- Page titles and headings
- Publication titles and authors
- Research area descriptions

Configure in `site/site.yml`:

```yaml
search:
  enabled: true
```
